Compilation:
$ javac HelloWorld.java  # produces HelloWorld.class
$ java HellWorld

Using packages is a common way to organize the namespace for classes:
# At the header of the HelloWorld class, include 'package com.example;'
. # the current directory (for this example)
|
----com
     |
     ----example
     |
      ----HelloWorld.java
      ----HelloWorld.class

javac @sorucefiles

Creating documentation with javadocs:
$ javadocs JavaFile.java

/**
 * Documentation
 *
 * @param
 *
 */

// inline comment
